restless /ˈrɛstlɪs/

1. ADJ If you are restless , you are bored, impatient, or dissatisfied, and you want to do something else. 焦躁不安的 

例： By 1982, she was restless and needed a new impetus for her talent. 到1982年，她焦躁不安，需要一个新的对其才华的推动力。 

2. restlessness N-UNCOUNT 焦躁不安 

例： From the audience came increasing sounds of restlessness. 从观众中传来了越来越大的焦躁不安的声音。 

3. ADJ If someone is restless , they keep moving around because they find it difficult to keep still. 坐立不安的 

例： My father seemed very restless and excited. 我父亲似乎非常坐立不安和兴奋。 

4. restlessness N-UNCOUNT 坐立不安 

例： Karen complained of hyperactivity and restlessness. 卡伦抱怨说自己过分好动和不安宁。

